{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"adec68a5-b360-4dd8-91c3-d8460316259e","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable** Microsoft.Testing.Platform in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — it now uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform under the hood. You can also run the test executable directly:\n\n   ```bash\n   ./bin/Debug/net8.0/YourTestProject\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` is the bridge for **xUnit v2** on MTP.\n- If you're open to upgrading to **xUnit v3**, use `xunit.v3` + `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` instead (v3 has breaking API changes — e.g., `Xunit` → `Xunit.v3` namespace).\n- The `TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses MTP instead of VSTest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b55cc671-18d2-449c-8e5b-2449bf7bbaf5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration path.","outputTokens":492,"requestId":"4C1E:1414DF:D5EEAA:109BEB0:6A012938"},"id":"3450e863-6b81-4809-8b45-f5a5e8c8e98f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:56:34.580Z","parentId":"e4042bf9-abc9-4bca-9cac-b40335220a96"}
